ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Visual Function Questionnaire - Test Date
In general, would you say your health is:
Notes: 1= Excellent; 2= Very Good; 3= Good; 4= Fair; 5= Poor ; 888=Don't Know/not sure; -999=Missing

ElementDescription: At the present time, would you say your eyesight using both eyes (with glasses or contact lenses, if you wear them) is:
Notes: 1 = Excellent ; 2 = Good ; 3 = Fair ; 4 = Poor ; 5 = Very poor ; 6 = Completely blind

ElementDescription: How much of the time do you worry about your eyesight?
Notes: 1 = None of the time; 2 = A little of the time; 3 = Some of the time; 4 = Most of the time; 5 = All of the time

ElementDescription: How much pain or discomfort have you had in and around your eyes (for example, burning, itching, or aching)? Would you say it is:
Notes: 1 = None; 2 = Mild; 3 = Moderate; 4 = Severe; 5 = Very severe

ElementDescription: How much difficulty do you have reading ordinary print in newspapers? Would you say you have:
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight; how difficult is it for you to do work or hobbies that require you to see up close; such as cooking or fixing things around the house?
Notes: 1=Not difficult at all; 2=A little bit difficult; 3=Somewhat difficult; 4=Very difficult; 5=Unable to do because of eyesight; 6=Unable to work or hobbies that require me to see up close because of another reason

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have finding something on a crowded shelf?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: How much difficulty do you have reading street signs or the names of stores?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have going down steps, stairs, or curbs in dim light or at night?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have noticing objects off to the side while you are walking along?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have seeing how people react to things you say?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have picking out and matching your own clothes?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have visiting with people in their homes, at parties, or in restaurants ?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have going out to see movies, plays, or sports events?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Are you currently driving, at least once in a while?
If you are not currently driving, have you never driven a car or have you given up driving?
If you gave up driving: Was that mainly because of your eyesight, mainly for some other reason, or because of both your eyesight and other reasons?
Notes: 1 = Mainly eyesight; 2 = Mainly other reasons; 3 = Both eyesight and other reasons

ElementDescription: If currently driving: How much difficulty do you have driving during the daytime in familiar places? Would you say you have:
Notes: 1 = No difficulty at all; 2 = A little difficulty; 3 = Moderate difficulty; 4 = Extreme difficulty

ElementDescription: How much difficulty do you have driving at night? Would you say you have:
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: How much difficulty do you have driving in difficult conditions, such as in bad weather, during rush hour, on the freeway, or in city traffic? Would you say you have:
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Do you accomplish less than you would like because of your vision?
Notes: 1 = All of the time; 2 = Most of the time; 3 = Some of the time; 4 = A little of the time; 5 = None of the time

ElementDescription: Are you limited in how long you can work or do other activities because of your vision?
Notes: 1 = All of the time; 2 = Most of the time; 3 = Some of the time; 4 = A little of the time; 5 = None of the time

ElementDescription: How much does pain or discomfort in or around your eyes, for example, burning, itching, or aching, keep you from doing what you'd like to be doing? Would you say:
Notes: 1 = All of the time; 2 = Most of the time; 3 = Some of the time; 4 = A little of the time; 5 = None of the time

ElementDescription: I stay home most of the time because of my eyesight
Notes: 1 = Definitely true; 2 = Mostly true; 3 = Not sure; 4 = Mostly false; 5 = Defnitely false

ElementDescription: I feel frustrated a lot of the time because of my eyesight
Notes: 1 = Definitely true; 2 = Mostly true; 3 = Not sure; 4 = Mostly false; 5 = Defnitely false

ElementDescription: I have much less control over what I do, because of my eyesight
Notes: 1 = Definitely true; 2 = Mostly true; 3 = Not sure; 4 = Mostly false; 5 = Defnitely false

ElementDescription: Because of my eyesight, I have to rely too much on what other people tell me
Notes: 1 = Definitely true; 2 = Mostly true; 3 = Not sure; 4 = Mostly false; 5 = Defnitely false

ElementDescription: I need a lot of help from others because of my eyesight
Notes: 1 = Definitely true; 2 = Mostly true; 3 = Not sure; 4 = Mostly false; 5 = Defnitely false

ElementDescription: I worry about doing things that will embarrass myself or others, because of my eyesight
Notes: 1 = Definitely true; 2 = Mostly true; 3 = Not sure; 4 = Mostly false; 5 = Defnitely false

ElementDescription: How would you rate your overall health, on a scale where zero is as bad as death and 10 is best possible health?

How would you rate your eyesight now (with glasses or contact lens on, if you wear them), on a scale of from 0 to 10, where zero means the worst possible eyesight, as bad or worse than being blind, and 10 means the best possible eyesight?
Wearing glasses, how much difficulty do you have reading the small print in a telephone book, on a medicine bottle, or on legal forms? Would you say:
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have figuring out whether bills you receive are accurate?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have doing things like shaving, styling your hair, or putting on makeup?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight; how difficult is it for you to recognize people from across a room?
Notes: 1=Not difficult at all; 2=A little bit difficult; 3=Somewhat difficult; 4=Very difficult; 5=Unable to do because of eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have taking part in active sports or other outdoor activities that you enjoy (like golf, bowling, jogging, or walking)?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Because of your eyesight, how much difficulty do you have entertaining friends and family in your home?
Notes: 1 =No difficulty at all ; 2 = A little difficulty ; 3 = Moderate difficulty ; 4 = Extreme difficulty ; 5 = Stopped doing this because of your eyesight ; 6 = Stopped doing this for other reasons, or not interested in doing this

ElementDescription: Do you have more help from others because of your vision?
Notes: 1 = All of the time; 2 = Most of the time; 3 = Some of the time; 4 = A little of the time; 5 = None of the time

ElementDescription: Are you limited in the kinds of things you can do because of your vision?
Notes: 1 = All of the time; 2 = Most of the time; 3 = Some of the time; 4 = A little of the time; 5 = None of the time
